## 🔹 8. API vs UI vs DB (Very important)

| Layer   | What it does |
| ------- | ------------ |
| UI      | Screen       |
| API     | Logic        |
| Backend | Processing   |
| DB      | Data         |
| Device  | Hardware     |

QA in healthcare tests all.

Your automation will test API layer.

---

## 🧠 Interview Question

**Q: What is API?**

Answer:

API is an interface that allows communication between UI, backend, database, and devices.
In healthcare systems APIs are used for login, role control, device communication, and data transfer.

